<section id="faq" class="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span class="gradient-text">Questions</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary>
          <span>What is Unbound and how does it work?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Unbound is a free, open-source DPI (Deep Packet Inspection) bypass tool for Russia. It uses the <strong>zapret2</strong> engine to manipulate TCP packets — specifically using techniques like TCP desynchronization and packet reordering (Multidisorder) — so that DPI systems like TSPU cannot properly analyze and block your traffic to sites like YouTube, Discord, Twitter, and Instagram.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>
          <span>How is this different from a VPN?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>VPNs route all your traffic through a foreign server, which slows down your connection. Unbound only modifies packets to blocked domains — your bank, government sites, and unblocked services work normally. <strong>Zero speed loss</strong> for your regular browsing.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>
          <span>Why does it need Administrator rights?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Unbound uses the WinDivert driver to intercept and modify network packets at the kernel level. This requires Administrator privileges. The program registers itself with Windows Task Scheduler for silent auto-start without repeated UAC prompts.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>
          <span>What if Auto-Tune doesn't find a working profile?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Auto-Tune tests 70+ profiles against multiple targets simultaneously. In rare cases, your ISP may require a specific combination. Try manual profile selection, check the "Dev Diary" log for details, and report your results on GitHub Issues.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>
          <span>Is this legal?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Unbound is an open-source tool (GPL-3.0) that modifies only your own outbound packets. It does not hack, spoof, or intercept other people's traffic. Whether using it violates local laws depends on your jurisdiction — consult local regulations.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>
          <span>What is "Discord Hygiene"?</span>
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>A built-in feature that automatically cleans the Discord client cache on startup. This prevents session poisoning and resolves the endless "Connecting..." issue that often plagues Discord users in blocked regions.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.faq {
  padding: 8rem 2rem;
  position: relative;
}

.container {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.section-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 4rem;
}

.section-tag {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
  background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1);
  border: 1px solid rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.2);
  border-radius: 100px;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #667eea;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.section-title {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #fff;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  letter-spacing: -1px;
}

.faq-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}

.faq-item {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.faq-item:hover {
  border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}

.faq-item[open] {
  border-color: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
  background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.03);
}

.faq-item summary {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  cursor: pointer;
  list-style: none;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #fff;
  font-size: 1rem;
  transition: color 0.2s;
}

.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
  display: none;
}

.faq-item summary svg {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.faq-item[open] summary svg {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.faq-answer {
  padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
}

.faq-answer p {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.faq-answer strong {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .faq {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }
}
</style>
